---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Shopify Website Builds" description="Custom Shopify stores designed for conversion and growth. Theme development, e-commerce optimisation, and ongoing support from Spires Digital.">
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Services', href: '/services' }, { label: 'Shopify Builds' }]} />

  <section class="page-hero" style="margin-top: -2rem;">
    <div class="container page-hero-content">
      <span class="badge">Shopify Development</span>
      <h1>Shopify Stores Built for Conversion</h1>
      <p>Custom Shopify stores that look great, load fast, and convert visitors into customers from day one.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <h2>What We Build</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2" style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        <div class="feature-card">
          <h3>Custom Theme Development</h3>
          <p>Bespoke Shopify themes built around your brand. Clean code, fast loading, and fully responsive across all devices.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <h3>E-Commerce Optimisation</h3>
          <p>Checkout flow optimisation, upsell/cross-sell setup, and conversion rate improvements to maximise revenue per visitor.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <h3>Migration & Setup</h3>
          <p>Seamless migration from WooCommerce, Magento, or other platforms. Product import, redirects, and SEO preservation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <h3>Ongoing Support</h3>
          <p>Post-launch support, app integration, and ongoing optimisation to keep your store performing at its best.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>What's Included</h2>
      <div class="included-grid">
        <div class="included-item">
          <h3>🎨 Design & UX</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Custom homepage and collection page design</li>
            <li>Mobile-first responsive layout</li>
            <li>Brand-aligned colour palette and typography</li>
            <li>Intuitive navigation and site architecture</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="included-item">
          <h3>🛒 E-Commerce Features</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Product page optimisation with rich media</li>
            <li>Checkout flow customisation</li>
            <li>Upsell and cross-sell functionality</li>
            <li>Discount codes and promotional setup</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="included-item">
          <h3>⚙️ Technical Setup</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Payment gateway integration (Stripe, PayPal, Shopify Payments)</li>
            <li>Shipping rules and tax configuration</li>
            <li>Email notification templates</li>
            <li>App integrations (Klaviyo, reviews, loyalty)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="included-item">
          <h3>🔍 SEO & Analytics</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>On-page SEO optimisation for all pages</li>
            <li>Structured data and schema markup</li>
            <li>GA4 and conversion tracking setup</li>
            <li>301 redirects for migrations</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Typical Project Timeline</h2>
      <div class="process-steps">
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Discovery & Planning — Week 1</h3>
            <p>We define your requirements, review your brand assets, map out the site architecture, and agree on the project scope and timeline.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Design & Prototyping — Weeks 2–3</h3>
            <p>Homepage and key page designs are created and refined based on your feedback. We ensure the design works beautifully on all devices.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Development & Build — Weeks 3–6</h3>
            <p>The Shopify store is built, with products loaded, payment gateways configured, and all functionality tested thoroughly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">4</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Testing & QA — Week 6–7</h3>
            <p>Cross-browser testing, mobile testing, checkout flow testing, and performance optimisation to ensure everything works flawlessly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">5</span>
          <div>
            <h3>Launch & Handover — Week 7–8</h3>
            <p>We launch your store, set up analytics tracking, provide training on the Shopify admin, and hand over documentation. Ongoing support begins.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tip-box">
        <strong>Typical timeline:</strong> Most standard Shopify builds are completed within 4–8 weeks. Custom builds with bespoke features may take 8–12 weeks depending on complexity.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section pricing-section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <h2>Shopify Build Pricing</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: 2rem;">Clear pricing with no surprises. Every project includes a fixed quote before we start.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-header">
            <span class="pricing-label">Standard Store</span>
            <span class="pricing-from">From</span>
            <span class="pricing-value">&pound;3,000</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="pricing-includes">
            <li>Theme customisation</li>
            <li>Up to 50 products loaded</li>
            <li>Payment and shipping setup</li>
            <li>Mobile-responsive design</li>
            <li>Basic SEO configuration</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card featured">
          <div class="pricing-header">
            <span class="pricing-label">Custom Build</span>
            <span class="pricing-from">From</span>
            <span class="pricing-value">&pound;5,000+</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="pricing-includes">
            <li>Bespoke theme development</li>
            <li>Unlimited product loading</li>
            <li>Custom functionality and apps</li>
            <li>Advanced SEO and schema</li>
            <li>Platform migration included</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-header">
            <span class="pricing-label">Ongoing Support</span>
            <span class="pricing-from">From</span>
            <span class="pricing-value">&pound;300<span class="pricing-period">/month</span></span>
          </div>
          <ul class="pricing-includes">
            <li>Monthly maintenance and updates</li>
            <li>Performance monitoring</li>
            <li>Bug fixes and improvements</li>
            <li>App updates and management</li>
            <li>Priority support access</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="pricing-caveat" style="text-align: center; margin-top: 1.5rem;">Every project is unique. <a href="/contact">Get in touch</a> for a detailed proposal and fixed quote.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section faq-section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How long does a Shopify build take?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>A standard Shopify store using a customised theme typically takes 4–6 weeks. Fully custom builds with bespoke functionality can take 8–12 weeks. We always agree on a clear timeline before starting, so you know exactly what to expect.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can you migrate from WooCommerce?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Absolutely. We handle WooCommerce to Shopify migrations regularly, including product data, customer accounts, order history, and 301 redirects to preserve your SEO rankings. We also migrate from Magento, BigCommerce, Squarespace, and other platforms.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do you do custom themes or use pre-built ones?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Both. For tighter budgets, we customise premium Shopify themes to match your brand — this is faster and more cost-effective. For brands needing a unique look and bespoke functionality, we build custom themes from scratch using Shopify's Liquid templating language.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What about ongoing support after launch?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>We offer ongoing support packages from &pound;300/month covering maintenance, updates, bug fixes, and improvements. Many of our clients stay on a support plan to ensure their store continues performing well and adapts to changing business needs. You're never locked in — support is month-to-month.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is Shopify good for SEO?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes — Shopify provides a solid SEO foundation with clean URLs, automatic sitemaps, and fast hosting. We enhance this with proper meta tags, structured data, image optimisation, and technical SEO best practices. Many of our Shopify clients rank well in competitive e-commerce niches.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do you set up payment gateways?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes, we configure all payment gateways including Shopify Payments, Stripe, PayPal, and any other providers you need. We also set up shipping rules, tax rates, and currency settings to ensure your checkout process is smooth and compliant.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section related-section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <h2>You Might Also Need</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-3" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        <a href="/services/meta-ads" class="related-card">
          <h3>Meta Ads</h3>
          <p>Drive targeted traffic to your new Shopify store with Facebook and Instagram advertising.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/services/ppc-management" class="related-card">
          <h3>PPC Management</h3>
          <p>Capture high-intent shoppers with Google Shopping and search ads for your Shopify store.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/services/affiliate-management" class="related-card">
          <h3>Affiliate Management</h3>
          <p>Add a performance-based sales channel to your Shopify store through strategic partnerships.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How long does a Shopify build take?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "A standard Shopify store using a customised theme typically takes 4–6 weeks. Fully custom builds with bespoke functionality can take 8–12 weeks. We always agree on a clear timeline before starting, so you know exactly what to expect."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can you migrate from WooCommerce?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Absolutely. We handle WooCommerce to Shopify migrations regularly, including product data, customer accounts, order history, and 301 redirects to preserve your SEO rankings. We also migrate from Magento, BigCommerce, Squarespace, and other platforms."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Do you do custom themes or use pre-built ones?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Both. For tighter budgets, we customise premium Shopify themes to match your brand — this is faster and more cost-effective. For brands needing a unique look and bespoke functionality, we build custom themes from scratch using Shopify's Liquid templating language."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What about ongoing support after launch?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "We offer ongoing support packages from £300/month covering maintenance, updates, bug fixes, and improvements. Many of our clients stay on a support plan to ensure their store continues performing well and adapts to changing business needs. You're never locked in — support is month-to-month."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is Shopify good for SEO?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes — Shopify provides a solid SEO foundation with clean URLs, automatic sitemaps, and fast hosting. We enhance this with proper meta tags, structured data, image optimisation, and technical SEO best practices. Many of our Shopify clients rank well in competitive e-commerce niches."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Do you set up payment gateways?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes, we configure all payment gateways including Shopify Payments, Stripe, PayPal, and any other providers you need. We also set up shipping rules, tax rates, and currency settings to ensure your checkout process is smooth and compliant."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Start Your Shopify Project</h2>
      <p>Tell us about your e-commerce goals and we'll put together a proposal.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-white btn-lg">Get a Quote</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .feature-card { padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--color-bg-alt); border-radius: var(--radius); }
  .feature-card h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .feature-card p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  .included-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
  .included-item { padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--color-bg-alt); border-radius: var(--radius); }
  .included-item h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .included-item ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .included-item li { padding: 0.35rem 0; font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--color-text-light); padding-left: 1.25rem; position: relative; }
  .included-item li::before { content: '✓'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--color-success); font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.85rem; }
  .process-steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
  .step { display: flex; gap: 1.25rem; align-items: start; }
  .step-num { width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--color-accent); color: white; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.9rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .step h3 { font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .step p { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  .tip-box { background: rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.05); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent); padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 0 var(--radius-sm) var(--radius-sm) 0; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
  .pricing-card { background: var(--color-white); border: 2px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 2rem; text-align: center; }
  .pricing-card.featured { border-color: var(--color-accent); position: relative; }
  .pricing-header { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .pricing-label { display: inline-block; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-accent); background: rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.1); padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 100px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .pricing-from { display: block; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-light); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .pricing-value { display: block; font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--color-accent); }
  .pricing-period { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  .pricing-includes { list-style: none; text-align: left; margin: 1.5rem 0; padding: 0; }
  .pricing-includes li { padding: 0.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-size: 0.95rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; position: relative; }
  .pricing-includes li::before { content: '✓'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--color-success); font-weight: 700; }
  .pricing-caveat { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  .pricing-caveat a { color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: underline; }
  .faq-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .faq-item { background: var(--color-bg-alt); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); overflow: hidden; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1rem 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0; margin-left: 1rem; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '−'; }
  .faq-answer { padding: 0 1.25rem 1rem; }
  .faq-answer p { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 1.7; }
  .faq-answer a { color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: underline; }
  .related-card { display: block; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--color-bg-alt); border-radius: var(--radius); transition: all 0.2s ease; border: 1px solid transparent; text-decoration: none; }
  .related-card:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent); transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: var(--shadow-md); }
  .related-card h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; color: var(--color-accent); }
  .related-card p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
</style>
